y entry in the dictionary delves into Weber scholarship and acts as a point of departure for discussion and research. As such, this book will be an invaluable resource to general readers, students, and scholars alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aSociologyvDictionaries. 0aSociologyxDictionariesxDictionariesxDictionaries. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Reference.2bisacsh1 aAgevall, Ola, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070397940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360022540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503600225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503600225.jpg  a978-3-11-070397-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles